Pika World Update- 17 September 2021ü©∫Markets FocusThe stronger than expected retail sales helped to give the equity market some level of support. Retail sales jumped 0.7% in August despite an expectation of a decline of 0.8%. In addition  Initial Jobless Claims is 20 000 higher than expected  reflecting a continuous mixed signal from the labour market. The robust and encouraging demand is a piece of good news despite many companies lowering their sales guidance for the quarter as supplies are limited to meet the robust demand.üíéAMC: Crypto Payment ModeYes  AMC Entertainment Holdings is expected to expand its acceptance for payment beyond Bitcoin  as it seeks to accept other digital tokens for online tickets payments by the year-end. This could include Etherum  Litecoin and Bitcoin Cash.This is a step forward for the crypto world as more organizations jump onto the crypto payment bandwagon.üöòLucid Air: An Upcoming Rising StarWhile the Tesla's Model S has a range of 405 miles  Lucid Air Dream Edition is set to have 520 miles  giving it a boost as the longest range electric vehicle rated by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA).This helps to boost its shares. In early September  Lucid has received its first buy rating from Wall Street as investors started to warm up towards the company  given that it has reached several milestones.üè¶Evergrande: Deteriorating FundamentalThe mega Chinese developer is reported to have applied for a suspension in trading its onshore bonds  which could pave the way for restructuring or even a default.Authorities have warned Chinese banks that the company is unlikely to pay interest on its loan due on 20 September. So  the liquidity crisis deepens as $300 billion liabilities weigh it down despite a relief that most of its foreign-denominated bonds repayment only comes next year.Nonetheless  the negativity strengthened around the company  and the group's stock price had dived by 80%  highlighting the overleveraging nature of the Chinese real estate sector.‚åöÔ∏èWhat's on the Menu Today?At 10 pm  we will welcome Michigan Consumer Expectation for September  which is expected to rise to 72.0 from 70.3. If this is realized  reading together with the recent strong retail sales could bode well for the economy.It is 17 September  Tuesday  at 7.40 am in Singapore and 7.40 pm in New York.
